Automatic Water Shutoff Valve Market Overview
The global Automatic Water Shutoff Valve Market was valued at approximately USD 2.4 billion in 2023 and is projected to reach USD 5.2 billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 11.6% during the forecast period. The market is witnessing steady growth due to the increasing demand for water conservation, the need for leak detection, and the growing adoption of smart home technologies. Technological advancements, such as the integration of IoT and AI into water management systems, are also expected to propel market expansion. The growing awareness about water wastage, climate change, and rising utility bills are driving the demand for automatic water shutoff valves, further boosting market growth.

